Position Summary
We are a dynamic and exciting corporate intellectual property and investment team managing multiple scientific, technology-oriented and healthcare start-ups with attention to alternative asset management and monetization best practices. In this capacity, we are looking for a motivated leader and intellectual property professional with high energy, discipline and business acumen to help us grow, consolidate and monetize our flourishing intellectual property activities.

NantWorks is seeking a highly motivated, experienced leader to serve as its Intellectual Property Counsel – Prosecution / Biotechnology. Working with a talented team, the individual in this position will have hands-on responsibility for patent prosecution and claim charting of biotechnology and pharmaceutical IP assets across the ecosystem of NantWorks companies. This will include directed prosecution (foreign or otherwise) and support for licensing and enforcement activities. This is a leadership position across the company and involves working with an expanding team of talented business, legal, technical and intellectual property-focused professionals. This is a great opportunity to join a high producing team and to work on novel issues in an exciting, fast-paced environment.

Essential Functions
Develop, maintain, vet, and counsel on a portfolio of worldwide biotechnology and pharmaceutical patents and applications for a global conglomerate;
Instigate and develop patent portfolio processes bringing rigor, clarity and focus on high value IP assets;
Assist in some enforcement activities such a claim charting;
Assist in building and maintaining world-class IP analytics capabilities and tools;
Grow, measure and track demonstrative IP value across a diverse set of assets;
Maintain strong working relationships with key international IP law firms in all primary geographies;
Support various patent monetization, IP licensing and investment programs;
Support IP due diligence activities in conjunction with corporate M&A
Responsible for supporting legal arguments for IPRs, validity challenges as well as opposition proceedings;
Work closely with corporate R&D functions to ensure that sufficient ideas and invention disclosures are generated and ultimately filed;
Some trademark counseling.

Education & Experience Requirements
Full qualification as a European or US Patent Attorney, with at least 7 years of post-qualification IP legal and patent prosecution experience; Prefer both in-house and law firm experience;
4+ years of experience managing high value global patent portfolios, emphasis on Bio and Pharma;
Juris Doctorate degree with membership in at least one state bar;
Master or Bachelor of Science in a Physical Science and/or Life Science discipline, preference given to Masters of Science in the Biology or Pharma technology spaces;
Diverse background including patent prosecution and support of successful patent enforcement actions through both licensing and litigation;
Experience growing, managing and claim charting a high quality patent portfolio;
Exceptional negotiation and communication skills;
Broad and deep legal expertise across multiple vertical segments;
Technical depth in one of more of the following disciplines: immunology, virology, proteomics, bioinformatics, small molecule pharm, monoclonal antibodies, recombinant microorganisms or histopathology.

NantWorks, LLC, is the umbrella organization for an ecosystem of companies committed to the convergence of 21st century innovative platforms to transform how we work, live and play: NantHealth, NantOmics, NantBioScience, NantCell and its affiliate NantKwest, NantPharma, NantMobile, NantStudio, NantCapital and NantCloud. Fact-based and solution driven, each of NantWorks’ division companies operates at the intersection of innovation and infrastructure. The core mission of NantWorks is convergence and a systems approach to human biology: to develop and deliver a diverse range of technologies that accelerates innovation, broaden the scope of scientific discovery, enhance ground-breaking research, and improve healthcare treatment for those in need. NantWorks is building an integrated fact-based, genomically and proteomically-informed, personalized approach to the delivery of care and the development of next generation diagnostics and therapeutics for life threatening diseases such as Cancer, Infectious Diseases and Alzheimer's.

All hires are based upon successful completion of our background check

The New York Genome Center (NYGC) is an independent, nonprofit academic research institution at the forefront of transforming biomedical research with the mission of advancing clinical care. A collaboration of premier academic, medical and industry leaders across the globe, the New York Genome Center is committed to advancing genomic research and offering clinical genomic testing so that new treatments, therapies and therapeutics against human disease can be developed. NYGC member organizations and partners are united in this unprecedented collaboration of technology, science and medicine, designed to harness the power of innovation and discoveries to advance genomic services.

The New York Genome Center is a VEVRAA Federal Contractor. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment and will not be discriminated against on the basis of race, creed, color, gender, religion, national origin, sexual orientation, age, disability, genetic predisposition or carrier status, protected veteran or military status, domestic violence victim status, partnership status, caregiver status, alienage or citizenship status, marital status, or any other characteristic protected by applicable law. The New York Genome Center takes affirmative action in support of its policy to hire and advance in employment individuals who are minorities, women, protected veterans, and individuals with disabilities.

Position Description

We are looking for a highly motivated, independent but team-oriented Associate Scientist with experience in next-generation sequencing (Illumina platform) to work in our production lab, operating, maintaining and loading the sequencers.

Job duties will include, but are not limited to:

Carry out procedures associated with DNA & RNA sequencing on the Illumina sequencing platform, including DNA/RNA library preparation, sample quantification & preparation, and Sequencer operation;
Maintain, troubleshoot and perform day-to-day work on the Sequencing equipment (e.g. Illumina NovaSeq, HiSeqX, HiSeq2500s, and cBots);
Plan and conduct flow cell loading utilizing automated liquid handlers (Hamilton Star);
Analyze current process procedures and provide feedback for their optimization and improvement, documenting processes, proposing method improvements, and troubleshooting assays, as needed;
Perform quality control of the samples and raw sequencing data;
Conduct other laboratory work, as needed;
Author/edit standard operating procedures;
Track all work and issues in the appropriate databases/tracking sheets; and,
Become proficient using NYGC’s LIMS tracking system to accurately perform day-to-day tasks.


Required Skills
Bachelors’ degree in Molecular Biology, Biotechnology, Biochemistry or related field, plus laboratory experience in nucleic acid research required;
2 years of experience in a molecular biology lab with at least 1+ years of demonstrated experience with next-generation sequencing library prep protocols and sequencing preferred;
Solid knowledge of molecular biology equipment and related protocols (including RNA and DNA preparation, RNA and DNA quantification, hybridization, PCR, multiplex amplification and bead-based solutions) highly preferred;
Array experience a plus, ideally on the Illumina Infinium platform;
Familiarity with Microsoft Word, Excel, and PowerPoint, preferably with Mac OS;
Exposure to bioinformatics is a plus;
Good general laboratory and organizational skills, including the ability to work independently and efficiently are essential;
Ability to multitask is a must, along with an orientation toward teamwork and cooperation;
Strong creative thinking and problem-solving skills; and,
Excellent communication skills required.
